    "log": {
      "entries": [
        {
          "key": 0,
          "channel": "narration",
          "text": "You open your eyes. Straw beneath you, the smell of wet rice, a low roof you do not know. A cold spring — the ninth year of An'ei — though the year is as lost to you as your name.",
          "tick": 0,
          "count": 1,
          "voice": "narrator"
        },
        {
          "key": 1,
          "channel": "narration",
          "text": "\"You're awake.\" Sōan the physician sits back on his heels. \"No kami carried you off, whatever the village wants to believe. A flood took you, and a blow to the head took the rest. Bodies forget. Given work and rice, they also mend.\"",
          "tick": 0,
          "count": 1,
          "speaker": "Sōan",
          "voice": "physician"
        },
        {
          "key": 2,
          "channel": "narration",
          "text": "You take stock of yourself: bruised, hollow, half-starved — but breathing.",
          "tick": 0,
          "count": 1,
          "voice": "narrator"
        },
        {
          "key": 3,
          "channel": "narration",
          "text": "Rice lies scattered across the Kurosawa grain-store floor. Spilled stores are waste — and clearing waste is a kind of work, if you set your hands to it.",
          "tick": 0,
          "count": 1,
          "voice": "narrator"
        },
        {
          "key": 4,
          "channel": "narration",
          "text": "\"Then I'll trust your craft, not the village's ghosts.\"",
          "tick": 0,
          "count": 1,
          "speaker": "You",
          "voice": "player"
        },
        {
          "key": 5,
          "channel": "narration",
          "text": "\"Sense, at last. Rest, eat, and let the swelling go down. The wits come back last — don't force them.\"",
          "tick": 0,
          "count": 1,
          "speaker": "Sōan",
          "voice": "physician"
        },
        {
          "key": 6,
          "channel": "milestone",
          "text": "Perk unlocked — Sōan's Counsel: A mind honed sharper than the body it wears. (+1 INT / −1 STR)",
          "tick": 0,
          "count": 1
        },
        {
          "key": 7,
          "channel": "narration",
          "text": "Something surfaces and is gone — a porter's knot, a road in grey rain, a name you cannot keep hold of.",
          "tick": 0,
          "count": 1,
          "voice": "narrator"
        },
        {
          "key": 8,
          "channel": "narration",
          "text": "\"Hold the road. The rain. Almost a name.\"",
          "tick": 0,
          "count": 1,
          "speaker": "You",
          "voice": "player"
        },
        {
          "key": 9,
          "channel": "narration",
          "text": "You chase it inward — and the ache in your skull chases you back. The name stays lost, but the habit of looking sets in.",
          "tick": 0,
          "count": 1,
          "voice": "narrator"
        },
        {
          "key": 10,
          "channel": "milestone",
          "text": "Perk unlocked — The Inward Turn: A mind that deepens by dwelling, at the price of a slower body. (+1 INT / −1 SPD)",
          "tick": 0,
          "count": 1
        },
        {
          "key": 11,
          "channel": "narration",
          "text": "On your feet, then. I am Genemon, steward of this house, and I keep the little it has left to keep. You'll not remember any of it, so hear it plain: the Kurosawa are samurai still — on the lord's rolls, if nowhere in the granary.",
          "tick": 0,
          "count": 1,
          "speaker": "Genemon",
          "voice": "steward"
        },
        {
          "key": 12,
          "channel": "narration",
          "text": "\"I'll earn my keep. Point me at it.\"",
          "tick": 0,
          "count": 1,
          "speaker": "You",
          "voice": "player"
        },
        {
          "key": 13,
          "channel": "narration",
          "text": "\"...Good. The house has had its fill of hands that don't. We'll see if you mean it.\"",
          "tick": 0,
          "count": 1,
          "speaker": "Genemon",
          "voice": "steward"
        },
        {
          "key": 14,
          "channel": "milestone",
          "text": "Perk unlocked — Genemon's Charge: Honest muscle set plainly to the task — sure over nimble. (+1 STR / −1 AGI)",
          "tick": 0,
          "count": 1
        },
        {
          "key": 16,
          "channel": "narration",
          "text": "So you put your hands to it. Rake what grain is still whole back toward the basket, a fistful at a time. We reckon a samurai house’s worth in koku — a year’s eating for one man — and every basket you save us is a measure we need not go begging to the lord to make good.",
          "tick": 0,
          "count": 1,
          "speaker": "Genemon",
          "voice": "steward"
        },
        {
          "key": 17,
          "channel": "narration",
          "text": "Your arms are leaden. You could rest a moment against the cool post.",
          "tick": 2,
          "count": 1,
          "voice": "narrator"
        },
        {
          "key": 19,
          "channel": "narration",
          "text": "Clear it without my standing over you, and you'll have earned your rice and a dry corner to sleep in. I'll make you no grander promise than that. In this house, none of us holds one.",
          "tick": 2,
          "count": 1,
          "speaker": "Genemon",
          "voice": "steward"
        },
        {
          "key": 21,
          "channel": "narration",
          "text": "\"...You don't shirk the work,\" Genemon says, eyeing the cleared boards and the filling basket. \"The house has had its fill of hands that do. Earn your keep, and a place here is yours.\"",
          "tick": 4,
          "count": 1,
          "voice": "narrator"
        },
        {
          "key": 131,
          "channel": "narration",
          "text": "The spilled stores are swept to rows; Genemon counts them without a word.",
          "tick": 2,
          "count": 1,
          "voice": "narrator"
        },
        {
          "key": 132,
          "channel": "narration",
          "text": "Dawn at the gate. The forecourt is swept clean — your doing — and Genemon waits by the posts, watching you the way a man watches weather.",
          "tick": 4,
          "count": 1,
          "voice": "narrator"
        },
        {
          "key": 133,
          "channel": "narration",
          "text": "\"You cleared the stores without being told twice. The house is short of hands and shorter of trustworthy ones. Stay — you're no day-hire now. Earn your rice.\"",
          "tick": 4,
          "count": 1,
          "speaker": "Genemon",
          "voice": "steward"
        },
        {
          "key": 134,
          "channel": "narration",
          "text": "\"The gate and the swept forecourt are yours to work now; stores come and go here. The home paddies too — the rice that feeds the house. And the kura's own repair is yours to tend: spend the house's small surplus to shore it up.\"",
          "tick": 4,
          "count": 1,
          "speaker": "Genemon",
          "voice": "steward"
        },
        {
          "key": 135,
          "channel": "narration",
          "text": "A pack-laden stranger has laid a mat in the lee of the gate-post — an Ōmi pedlar, come because a tended gate draws trade. He lifts a hand as you pass.",
          "tick": 4,
          "count": 1,
          "voice": "narrator"
        },
        {
          "key": 136,
          "channel": "narration",
          "text": "\"A tended gate's a lucky gate for a man with a pack. Tokubei, of Ōmi — mind if I keep my mat here a while, young master? Coin of your own spends as well as any lord's.\"",
          "tick": 4,
          "count": 1,
          "speaker": "Tokubei",
          "voice": "villager"
        },
        {
          "key": 137,
          "channel": "narration",
          "text": "\"The house has my hands.\"",
          "tick": 4,
          "count": 1,
          "speaker": "You",
          "voice": "player"
        },
        {
          "key": 138,
          "channel": "narration",
          "text": "\"...Good. Hands that don't need watching are the rarest thing I keep.\"",
          "tick": 4,
          "count": 1,
          "speaker": "Genemon",
          "voice": "steward"
        },
        {
          "key": 139,
          "channel": "narration",
          "text": "The gate and the swept forecourt are yours to work now — stores come and go here.",
          "tick": 4,
          "count": 1,
          "voice": "narrator"
        },
        {
          "key": 140,
          "channel": "narration",
          "text": "The terraced home paddies open to you — the rice that feeds the house.",
          "tick": 4,
          "count": 1,
          "voice": "narrator"
        },
        {
          "key": 141,
          "channel": "narration",
          "text": "You begin to mark the turning of the days, and the four seasons with them.",
          "tick": 4,
          "count": 1,
          "voice": "narrator"
        },
        {
          "key": 142,
          "channel": "milestone",
          "text": "Rank ↑ — Kept hand 下人",
          "tick": 4,
          "count": 1,
          "contentKey": "rank.marker",
          "params": {
            "title": "Kept hand",
            "kanji": "下人"
          }
        },
        {
          "key": 143,
          "channel": "narration",
          "text": "The estate's own state of repair is yours to tend now — spend the house's surplus to shore it up.",
          "tick": 4,
          "count": 1,
          "voice": "narrator"
        },
        {
          "key": 144,
          "channel": "narration",
          "text": "The rice you clear and grow is food, not only trade — a plain bowl of it fills a hollow belly and puts you back to work the faster.",
          "tick": 4,
          "count": 1,
          "voice": "narrator"
        },
        {
          "key": 420,
          "channel": "narration",
          "text": "The paddies answer your hand now; the green rows stand straighter for it.",
          "tick": 2,
          "count": 1,
          "voice": "narrator"
        },
        {
          "key": 423,
          "channel": "narration",
          "text": "Copper coin, warm from another hand — your first wage. Rice fills a belly; coin is what the world takes in trade for everything a belly is not.",
          "tick": 6,
          "count": 1,
          "voice": "narrator"
        },
        {
          "key": 503,
          "channel": "system",
          "text": "You rest against the post. The ache dulls; the light through the slats shifts.",
          "tick": 4,
          "count": 1,
          "voice": "narrator",
          "ephemeral": true
        },
        {
          "key": 504,
          "channel": "reward",
          "text": "Haul stores at the forecourt. (+2 coin)",
          "tick": 12,
